    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1810_03_21_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                   <dateline> 
                   <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName> <note>35</note>
                    <date when="1810-03-21">March 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> .. 1810</date></dateline></opener>
                
                <p>
                    
                    My dear and good <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Sir,</persName> Your kind note has<lb/>
                    this moment reached us - You call it a <hi rend="underline"><choice><orig>griffon-<lb/>
                    age</orig><reg>griffonage</reg></choice></hi> but I beg you will never trouble yourself<lb/>
                    to write more carefully: for I assure you my<lb/>
                    secretary reads your most hurried hand<lb/>
                    as easily as she reads print.<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    Thank you for allowing me to use<lb/>
                    your observations on <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PascB1">Pascal,</persName> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BossJ1">Bossuet</persName> &amp;c - I have<lb/>
                    inserted them in clerical Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>.: but I certainly<lb/>
                    waited for your permission as I think even<lb/>
                    the best friends cannot be too exact on some<lb/>
                    points - I shall send that chapter tomorrow<lb/>
                    to Johnson &amp; Co. as I have made all the alterations<lb/>
                    in it which you advised -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    No printer upon earth however<lb/>
                    shall hurry me to send him any more<lb/>
                    of the book, whilst I have the most remote<lb/>
                    hope that you will <hi rend="underline">at your leisure</hi> give<lb/>
                    me any more of your remarks upon it -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    I shall set to work directly<lb/>
                    upon the hints you have so kindly &amp; so ably given<lb/>
                    about luxury - your obliged &amp; grateful<lb/>
                    <note>Turn</note>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">Rich<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Lovell Edgeworth</persName><lb/></p>
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1810_03_21_page02.jpg"/>
                    <p>
                    Veto et etiam veto<lb/></p>
                    
                    
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1810_03_21_page03.jpg"/>
                     <closer>
